    <div class="acc-h" onclick="tg(this)"><span>🧱</span><span class="acc-title">2 · Thoracic Spine + Upper Back</span><span class="acc-time">5 min ★</span><span style="color:var(--muted);font-size:10px">▼</span></div>
    <div class="acc-b">
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">📖</div><div><div class="an">Book Openers — Side-Lying Thoracic Rotation</div><div class="ad">Lie on side, knees at 90°. Sweep top arm overhead and behind, chest opens toward ceiling. Hold 2–3 sec. The single best active thoracic drill — especially important with 5-day heavy lifting compressing the thoracic.</div></div><div class="at">8/side</div></div>
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🪵</div><div><div class="an">Foam Roller Thoracic Extension</div><div class="ad">Roller at mid-back. Arms crossed. Lean back and extend over roller. Move up/down 2–3 inches, pause on tight spots. Go deeper post-session than pre-session — muscles are warm now.</div></div><div class="at">90 sec</div></div>
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🧵</div><div><div class="an">Thread the Needle</div><div class="ad">On all fours, thread one arm under body, let shoulder touch the ground. Releases rhomboids and mid-traps taxed by rows and pull-ups. Hold 30 sec each side.</div></div><div class="at">30 sec/side</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="acc-card">
    <div class="acc-h" onclick="tg(this)"><span>🏋️</span><span class="acc-title">3 · Shoulder + Rotator Cuff Recovery</span><span class="acc-time">4 min</span><span style="color:var(--muted);font-size:10px">▼</span></div>
    <div class="acc-b">
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🦅</div><div><div class="an">Eagle Arms</div><div class="ad">Arms forward at shoulder height, wrap one arm under the other at elbows, lift. Posterior rotator cuff and upper back. Essential after OHP and lateral raise volume.</div></div><div class="at">45 sec/side</div></div>
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🤗</div><div><div class="an">Cross-Body Shoulder Stretch</div><div class="ad">Pull one arm across chest with opposite hand at elbow. Rear delt and rotator cuff recovery. 30 sec each side.</div></div><div class="at">30 sec/side</div></div>
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🌀</div><div><div class="an">Sleeper Stretch</div><div class="ad">Lie on side, bottom arm at 90°. Gently press the back of the wrist toward the floor with top hand — internal rotation stretch for the posterior capsule. High volume pressing tightens this over time. Don't force it.</div></div><div class="at">45 sec/side</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="acc-card">
    <div class="acc-h" onclick="tg(this)"><span>🦵</span><span class="acc-title">4 · Hips + Posterior Chain</span><span class="acc-time">4 min</span><span style="color:var(--muted);font-size:10px">▼</span></div>
    <div class="acc-b">
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🕊️</div><div><div class="an">Pigeon Pose</div><div class="ad">Front shin roughly parallel to mat, rear leg extended. Hip rotator recovery after squat and RDL volume. 60 sec each side — non-negotiable on leg day.</div></div><div class="at">60 sec/side</div></div>
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🐕</div><div><div class="an">Downward Dog into Forward Fold</div><div class="ad">45 sec downward dog (heels toward floor). Walk feet in, hang in forward fold 45 sec. Full hamstring and posterior chain release after heavy RDL and squat sessions.</div></div><div class="at">90 sec</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="acc-card">
    <div class="acc-h" onclick="tg(this)"><span>💪</span><span class="acc-title">5 · Bicep + Forearm Recovery</span><span class="acc-time">2 min</span><span style="color:var(--muted);font-size:10px">▼</span></div>
    <div class="acc-b">
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🤲</div><div><div class="an">Bicep Stretch — Wall or Doorframe</div><div class="ad">Place palm flat on wall behind you (thumb down), gently rotate away. Stretches the long head of the bicep which curl clusters and rest-pause load heavily. 30 sec each side.</div></div><div class="at">30 sec/side</div></div>
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🤚</div><div><div class="an">Wrist Flexor + Extensor Stretch</div><div class="ad">Arm extended palm up, pull fingers back 20 sec. Then palm down, pull fingers toward you 20 sec. Farmer's carries and reverse curls load the forearm extensors hard — this clears the pump.</div></div><div class="at">20 sec each × 2</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="acc-card">
    <div class="acc-h" onclick="tg(this)"><span>🌙</span><span class="acc-title">6 · Spinal Decompression — Close Every Session</span><span class="acc-time">1 min</span><span style="color:var(--muted);font-size:10px">▼</span></div>
    <div class="acc-b">
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🧘</div><div><div class="an">Child's Pose</div><div class="ad">Kneel, fold forward, arms extended. Gravity decompresses the spine. 30 sec. Five heavy days compress the spine significantly — this reverses it before sauna.</div></div><div class="at">30 sec</div></div>
      <div class="arow"><div class="aico">🙌</div><div><div class="an">Passive Bar Hang</div><div class="ad">Wide grip, feet lightly on floor. Spine and lats fully decompress. No bar? Child's pose another 30 sec. Then go to sauna.</div></div><div class="at">30 sec</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SAUNA -->
<div id="sa" class="page">
  <div class="stag">Sauna Protocol · After Every Session</div>
  <div class="note gold"><strong>Why it works with this block:</strong> 5-day high-intensity training creates significant systemic inflammation. Post-workout sauna raises HSP (heat shock proteins) that accelerate muscle repair, reduces DOMS by up to 30%, and creates a synergistic HGH spike when combined with resistance training. 15 minutes is the sweet spot — meaningful benefit without cortisol cost.</div>
  <div class="scards">
    <div class="scard"><div class="scard-ico">💧</div><div class="scard-t">Hydrate First</div><div class="scard-d">Drink 16–20 oz before entering. Bring water in.</div></div>
    <div class="scard"><div class="scard-ico">⏱️</div><div class="scard-t">Wait After Yoga</div><div class="scard-d">5–10 min after yoga. Heart rate below ~100 bpm before entering.</div></div>
    <div class="scard"><div class="scard-ico">🌡️</div><div class="scard-t">170–185°F · 15 Min</div><div class="scard-d">Exit immediately if dizzy or nauseous. No forcing through discomfort.</div></div>
    <div class="scard"><div class="scard-ico">🧠</div><div class="scard-t">No Phone</div><div class="scard-d">Slow breathing. Visualize next session. Cortisol drops in stillness.</div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="note"><strong>After sauna:</strong> Cool down 5 min. Drink 16–24 oz water. Eat within 60 min of finishing. Sleep 8+ hours — this is when the adaptation actually happens.</div>
  <div class="note green"><strong>On high-volume days (Mon, Wed, Fri):</strong> Sauna is especially valuable. The combination of lifting + abs + yoga + sauna on these days fully closes the recovery loop before the next session.</div>
</div>

